"11:117:8" : {s: 11, a: 117, w: 8, r: "صلح", t: "مُصْلِحُونَ", l: "مُصْلِح", lc: 5, tl: "muṣ'liḥūna", lb: "মীমাংসা কারী",e: "(were) reformers", b: "সংশোধনকারী", i: "orang-orang yang berbuat kebaikan", f: 2, rm: "to be right/good/honest/upright/sound/righteous, suit, fit. aslaha - to set a thing aright, reform, do good. saalihaat - good works, fit and suiting deeds. aslaha (vb. 4) - to make whole sound, set things right, effect an agreement between, render fit. islaah - uprightness, reconciliation, amendment, reformation. muslihun - reformer, one who is upright, righteous, a person of integrity, peacemaker, suitable."},
